C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20want%20their%20kids%20to%20be%20successful.%20They%20want%20them%20to%20be%20at%20the%20top%20of%20their%20class%20or%20on%20the%20best%20soccer%20team.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEverything%20is%20about%20their%20children's%20future%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20what%20their%20kids%20like%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20once%20saw%20a%20high%20schooler%20in%20my%20counseling%20practice%20who%20was%20so%20burned%20out.%20She%20was%20on%20the%20cheer%20team%2C%20so%20had%20to%20go%20to%20practices%20and%20games%2C%20but%20she%20also%20did%20competitive%20dance%2C%20which%20was%20what%20she%20really%20loved.%20She%20wanted%20to%20quit%20cheerleading%20but%20said%20her%20parents%20wouldn't%20let%20her%20because%20they%20were%20concerned%20about%20how%20dropping%20out%20would%20impact%20her%20college%20prospects.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParents%20are%20coming%20from%20a%20place%20of%20fear%20that%20their%20kids%20will%20get%20left%20behind.%20They%20want%20their%20kid%20to%20have%20a%20leg%20up.%20It's%20a%20rampant%20fear%20in%20our%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20it's%20important%20for%20kids%20to%20pick%20their%20activities%20but%20also%20have%20some%20free%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20recently%20spoke%20to%20another%20family%20with%20a%20daughter%20in%20sixth%20grade.%20She%20does%20volleyball%20and%20gymnastics%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20I%20told%20her%20dad%20there%20was%20something%20missing%20in%20her%20list%20of%20activities%3A%20play%20and%20downtime.%20Time%20to%20do%20things%20she%20enjoys%2C%20like%20reading%20or%20doing%20artwork%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20in%20her%20portfolio%2C%20but%20because%20she%20likes%20to%20draw.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funsupervised-play-outdoors-kids-neighborhood-benefits-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUnsupervised%20play%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20great%20way%20for%20kids%20to%20learn%2C%20but%20they%20have%20little%20time%20for%20it%20these%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0a15669-9af8-48bd-8675-7847bb67792b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Trying%20to%20be%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20your%20child's%20motivation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20parents%20push%20their%20kids%2C%20they'll%20ask%20me%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EHow%20do%20I%20motivate%20my%20daughter%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20tell%20them%20they're%20asking%20the%20wrong%20question.%20It's%20not%20your%20job%20to%20motivate%20your%20kids.%20A%20better%20question%20would%20be%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20support%20my%20child's%20intrinsic%20motivation%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20good%20way%20to%20support%20a%20child's%20motivation%20is%20to%20ask%20them%20questions%20to%20make%20them%20think%20about%20why%20they%20want%20A's%20at%20school%20or%20why%20they%20like%20soccer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20speaking%20to%20a%20girl%20who%20was%20a%20gymnast.%20We%20asked%20what%20she%20liked%20about%20gymnastics.%20She%20started%20talking%2C%20but%20her%20dad%20interjected%20and%20told%20her%20to%20show%20us%20her%20trophies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20could%20tell%20her%20awards%20weren't%20what%20drove%20her%2C%20so%20we%20repeated%20the%20question.%20She%20said%20her%20favorite%20thing%20was%20the%20floor%20routine.%20She%20liked%20it%20when%20all%20eyes%20were%20on%20her%2C%20and%20she%20entertained%20people.%20That%20was%20her%20intrinsic%20motivation%20for%20loving%20gymnastics.%20We%20derive%20more%20satisfaction%20from%20things%20if%20we're%20doing%20them%20for%20our%20reasons%20instead%20of%20to%20please%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EListen%20to%20why%20your%20kid%20enjoys%20something%20and%20use%20that%20understanding%20to%20encourage%20them.%20You're%20not%20always%20going%20to%20be%20there%20to%20push%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelicopter-parent-over-involved-college-daughter-life-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emicromanage%20your%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20They%20need%20to%20learn%20to%20push%20themselves%20by%20focusing%20on%20why%20they%20want%20to%20do%20things%20and%20how%20it's%20meaningful%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f173279-e2e1-4809-bc0c-884aa4ebc3c0%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Overindulging%20your%20child's%20requests%20for%20new%20things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20found%20that%20the%20executives%20I%20work%20with%20are%20very%20worried%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-spoiling-your-kids-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhether%20their%20kids%20will%20be%20spoiled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20if%20they'll%20have%20ambition.%20Many%20of%20these%20parents%20worked%20hard%20but%20are%20conscious%20that%20their%20kids%20don't%20have%20to%20do%20that%20because%20they're%20born%20into%20affluence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20have%20even%20said%20they're%20worried%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflying-first-business-class-etiquette-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eflying%20first%20class%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20could%20spoil%20their%20child.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20tell%20them%20it's%20amazing%20their%20child%20can%20receive%20education%20through%20wonderful%20trips.%20That%20won't%20spoil%20them%2C%20but%20what%20will%20is%20if%20you%20immediately%20comply%20every%20time%20your%20child%20asks%20for%20something%20new.%3C%2Fspan%3E