sed%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20(Marjory)%20Jerry%20Cascio-Hitchcock%2C%20a%2092-year-old%20teacher%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20things%20have%20made%20my%2060-year%20teaching%20career%20possible%3A%20first%2C%20I%20truly%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20an%20early%20childhood%20teacher%20for%20many%20years%2C%20and%20when%20I%20felt%20at%20the%20top%20of%20my%20game%2C%20I%20found%20that%20I%20was%20most%20interested%20in%20the%20kids%20with%20learning%20difficulties.%20Other%20teachers%20would%20explain%20that%20a%20student%20had%20been%20awful%2C%20and%20I'd%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20fascinating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20could%20change%20my%20focus%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20get%20bored.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere%20are%20always%20new%20challenges%20at%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20not%20bored%20%E2%80%94%20at%20age%2092%2C%20I%20haven't%20retired%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22934181b1-7155-48b1-8049-718516cc33e5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20didn't%20plan%20to%20become%20a%20teacher%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foberlin-college-bakery-defamation-suit-appeal-rejected-ohio-supreme-court-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOberlin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20took%20office%20jobs%2C%20and%20thought%20about%20being%20a%20librarian.%20When%20my%20son%20was%20in%20nursery%20school%2C%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20help.%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20surprise%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20become%20a%20teacher.%20I%20graduated%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20English%20literature%20and%20a%20minor%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%2C%20I%20loved%20it%20so%20much.%20I%20remember%20walking%20home%20one%20day%20and%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BWow%2C%20I%20can't%20believe%20I'm%20paid%20to%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20taught%20at%20Churchill%2C%20a%20school%20for%20children%20with%20learning%20disabilities%2C%20for%20two%20years%20before%20entering%20private%20tutoring.%20I%20next%20joined%20LREI%2C%20a%20school%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20almost%2020%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20My%20commute%20usually%20takes%2030%20minutes%2C%20although%20I%20allow%20for%2045%20to%20get%20to%20work.%20I%20used%20to%20do%20summer%20tutoring%2C%20but%20now%20I%20rest%20during%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d21cfa55-ac6f-4ca7-9e7f-4fee6bc1ef54%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20tell%20my%20students%20to%20find%20something%20they%20love%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20students%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20should%20I%20do%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20always%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BFind%20something%20you%20love.%26quot%3B%20If%20you're%20privileged%20enough%20to%20follow%20what%20you%20love%20and%20make%20some%20sacrifices%20to%20do%20so%2C%20do%20it.%20Those%20who%20can%20are%20so%20lucky%2C%20and%20I%20count%20myself%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20worked%20in%20off-Broadway%20theater%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20bring%20in%20much%20money.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20we%20lived%20below%20the%20poverty%20level%20with%20our%20two%20kids%2C%20but%20my%20family%20was%20well-to-do.%20They%20seldom%20helped%20us%20financially%2C%20but%20we%20were%20fortunate%20to%20know%20they%20could%20help%20if%20necessary.%20That's%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbiracial-didnt-understand-generational-wealth-growing-up-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerational%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20very%20aware%20of%20that%2C%20and%20I%20always%20mention%20it%20to%20my%20students%20because%20I%20work%20at%20a%20private%20school.%20Many%20come%20from%20families%20like%20mine%2C%20and%20they%20aren't%20always%20aware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214dc8f10-e9d3-4494-a760-4336ad6f0378%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EToday%2C%20I%20share%20a%20learning%20center%20with%20two%20other%20teachers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20regular%20classes%20with%20students%20with%20learning%20disabilities.%20Our%20open%20plan%20keeps%20the%20learning%20center%20open%20from%208%20a.m.%20to%205%20p.m.%20Any%20kid%20can%20come%20anytime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20see%20some%20of%20the%20smartest%20kids%20in%20the%20class%20come%20in%20needing%20help%20with%20math.%20It%20reduces%20the%20stigma%20for%20other%20kids%20with%20more%20profound%20learning%20issues%20because%20they%20know%20that%20anyone%20can%20come%20in%20at%20any%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2221bf8e3d-2b9c-4573-ab1e-ce57123453cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20our%20students%20have%20some%20sort%20of%20learning%20disability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20fascinating%20kids%2C%20and%20I%20am%20fascinated%20with%20them.%20The%20human%20brain%20is%20so%20specific%20%E2%80%94%20you%20think%20you%20know%20the%20patterns%2C%20but%20then%20you%20get%20a%20kid%20who%20is%20good%20at%20some%20things%20and%20not%20others.%20It's%20my%20job%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20best%20to%20teach%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20teaching%2C%20dyslexia%20had%20been%20recently%20quantified%2C%20with%20good%20research%20showing%20what%20parts%20of%20the%20brain%20good%20readers%20use%20and%20how%20parts%20of%20the%20brain%20kids%20with%20trouble%20use%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20teachers%20have%20been%20saying%20this%20for%20years%3A%20it%20isn't%20that%20this%20kid%20isn't%20trying%3B%20they're%20just%20doing%20it%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b62864ea-780a-42cb-8a80-8c4a22528dd5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20kids%20have%20crippling%20anxiety%2C%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20when%20I%20was%20in%20high%20school%2C%20we%20weren't%20as%20anxious%20for%20many%20reasons.%20Today%2C%20kids%20are%20so%20anxious%20about%20tests.%20Some%20even%20avoid%20school.%20There%20are%20often%20bigger%20reasons%2C%20such%20as%20two%20kids%20I've%20been%20working%20with%2C%20who%20have%20both%20recently%20lost%20their%20fathers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20is%20such%20a%20big%20part%20of%20anxiety.%20We're%20only%20just%20realizing%20how%20destructive%20social%20media%20can%20be%20for%20adolescents.%20One%20thing%20we've%20done%20at%20my%20school%20this%20year%20is%20have%20kids%20check%20their%20phones%20when%20they%20come%20in%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20get%20them%20back%20until%20they%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20lucky%20that%20I've%20never%20had%20that%20problem.%20I%20love%20reading%20books.%20I%20use%20the%20internet%20for%20email%20and%20some%20research%2C%20which%20is%20wonderful%2C%20but%20that's%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bdce5106-3b00-4744-b62b-94b1c730e392%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20reason%20for%20my%20long%20career%20is%20that%20I%20love%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20come%20to%20work%20daily%20so%20happy%20and%20wonder%20how%20many%20people%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20a%20girl%20who%20took%20the%20Regents%20Examination%20called%20me%20when%20she%20got%20her%20results.%20It%20was%20before%20cellphones.%20She%20went%20to%20the%20nearest%20phone%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJerry%2C%20we%20got%20an%2085!%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20her%20that%20'we'%20didn't%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20all%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20offered%20good%20money%20to%20go%20into%20school%20administration%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20for%20me.%20Desk%20work%20is%20everything%20I%20hate.%20I'm%20lucky%20to%20have%20been%20able%20to%20turn%20these%20offers%20down%3B%20many%20good%20teachers%20can't%20for%20financial%20reasons.%20I'm%20very%20privileged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b516e1c-e701-4f49-aac2-3b4b35bef6c5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20will%20be%