ts%20to%20make%20its%20e-commerce%20business%20more%20efficient%20and%20profitable.%20This%20huge%20initiative%20started%20out%20a%20lot%20smaller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20company%20launched%20a%20competition%20for%20university%20engineering%20teams%20called%20the%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge.%20It%20called%20on%20researchers%20to%20design%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-amazon-uses-robots-sort-transport-packages-warehouses-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobots%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20common%20warehouse%20task%3A%20Grabbing%20products%20from%20a%20shelf%20and%20putting%20them%20in%20a%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20tech%20reporter%2C%20this%20quirky%20project%20intrigued%20me.%20At%20the%20time%20in%20early%202015%2C%20Google%20was%20testing%20self-driving%20cars%2C%20a%20technology%20that%20emerged%20from%20a%20similar%20academic%20competition%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-first-self-driving-cars-that-competed-in-darpa-grand-challenge-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDARPA%20Grand%20Challenge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20What%20if%20Amazon%20was%20trying%20to%20replicate%20this%20magic%2C%20but%20with%20robots%20rather%20than%20automobiles%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222775%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Researchers%20examine%20a%20robot%20during%20an%20Amazon%20contest%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf7dc0b1834fe311659246%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222081%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20examine%20a%20robot%20during%20an%20Amazon%20contest%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20funny%20thing%20happened.%20The%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%20faded%20away.%20It%20was%20renamed%20and%20only%20lasted%20a%20few%20years.%20I%20chalked%20this%20up%20to%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-jack-clark-anthropic-ai-billionaire-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebad%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20moved%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20thought%20about%20this%20challenge%20again%20late%20last%20year.%20That's%20when%20Amazon%20unveiled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-robots-could-save-10-billion-a-year-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enext-generation%20warehouse%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Louisiana%20that%20has%2010%20times%20more%20robots%20moving%20products%20around%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20picking%20them%20up%20with%20dexterity.%20The%20facility%20processes%20orders%2025%25%20faster%20and%2025%25%20more%20efficiently%2C%20and%20it%20will%20likely%20be%20the%20future%20of%20the%20company's%20e-commerce%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224558%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picking%20robot%20at%20work%20during%20an%20Amazon%20robotics%20contest%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf8e9f69253ccddf97b50e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222987%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20picking%20robot%20at%20work%20during%20an%20Amazon%20robotics%20contest%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20years%20after%20the%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%2C%20the%20fruits%20of%20this%20nerdy%20competition%20have%20finally%20emerged.%20It%20follows%20an%20uncannily%20similar%20timeline%20to%20the%20DARPA%20Grand%20Challenge%2C%20which%20started%20in%202004%20and%20resulted%20in%20Google's%20driverless%20cars%20hitting%20the%20road%20roughly%20a%20decade%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Business%20Insider%20reporter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feugene-kim%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEugene%20Kim%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20investigated%20how%20Amazon's%20huge%20new%20fleet%20of%20picking%20robots%20came%20to%20be%2C%20and%20how%20this%20competition%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-automation-is-changing-manufacturing-healthcare-and-transportation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautomation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that's%20about%20to%20crash%20over%20the%20warehouse%20and%20logistics%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af947357-3461-4aa6-ac97-8665e809a804%5C%22%3EFrom%20pallets%20to%20picking%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20Kiva%20robots%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54cac7d3eab8ea473a9e7cc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20Kiva%20robots%3Cp%3EYouTube%2FBusinesswire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20with%20an%20acquisition.%20In%202012%2C%20Amazon%20paid%20%24775%20million%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-buys-kiva-systems-775-million-2012-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKiva%20Systems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20designed%20flat%20robots%20that%20zip%20around%20warehouse%20floors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20helped%20move%20pallets%20of%20goods%20around%2C%20but%20humans%20still%20needed%20to%20pick%20items.%20Getting%20a%20robot%20to%20spot%20the%20correct%20product%20in%20a%20box%2C%20then%20grab%20it%20just%20hard%20enough%20to%20pick%20it%20up%2C%20but%20not%20damage%20it%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20incredibly%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20the%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%20came%20in.%20Instead%20of%20hacking%20away%20at%20this%20problem%20itself%2C%20the%20company%20wanted%20to%20focus%20the%20broader%20academic%20community%20on%20the%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20was%20that%20any%20valuable%20inventions%20would%20be%20out%20in%20the%20public%20sphere%2C%20and%20Amazon%20might%20not%20directly%20benefit%20from%20them.%20But%20the%20potential%20gains%20were%20much%20bigger%2C%20according%20to%20executives%20and%20roboticists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222974%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brad%20Porter%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Cobot%2C%20stands%20by%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20robots.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ad4f7c6630eb10385c7a77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221972%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrad%20Porter%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Cobot%2C%20stands%20by%20one%20of%20the%20startup's%20robots.%3Cp%3ECobot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmazon%20doesn't%20compete%20with%20robotics%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20former%20Amazon%20Robotics%20chief%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-amazon-robotics-chief-raises-100-million-startup-brad-porter-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrad%20Porter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20runs%20robotics%20startup%20Cobot%20now.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20facing%20an%20unsolved%20research%20problem%20in%20robotics%20AI%20like%20bin%20picking%2C%20Amazon%20benefits%20if%20anyone%20solves%20that%20problem%20as%20long%20as%20Amazon%20can%20get%20access%20to%20the%20technology%20to%20improve%20their%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20Amazon%20was%20trying%20to%20solve%20was%20how%20to%20motivate%20researchers%20to%20focus%20on%20this%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Porter%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Picking%20Challenge%20very%20much%20succeeded%20in%20doing%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dfe960b0-aacd-4ae1-9da4-7c630ef078c0%5C%22%3EOreos%2C%20Sharpies%2C%20and%20dog%20toys%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20competition%20took%20place%20over%20two%20days%20in%20late%20May%202015%20in%20Seattle%2C%20with%20more%20than%2025%20teams%20from%20colleges%20including%20MIT%2C%20Duke%2C%20Rutgers%2C%20and%20Georgia%20Tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contestants%20had%20to%20design%20a%20robot%20that%20could%20pick%20products%20from%20a%20typical%20shelf%20found%20on%20a%20Kiva%20Systems%20warehouse%20pod%2C%20and%20then%20put%20those%20items%20into%20containers.%20The%20picker%20had%20to%20be%20fully%20autonomous%2C%20and%20each%20robot%20was%20given%2020%20minutes%20to%20pick%2012%20target%20items%20from%20the%20shelves.%20Contestants%20had%20to%20open-source%20their%20creations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%2C%20including%20ABB%2C%20Fanuc%2C%20and%20Rethink%20Robotics%2C%20founded%20by%20industry%20pioneer%20Rodney%20Brooks%2C%20provided%20hardware%20for%20contestants%20to%20repurpose%20and%20tinker%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20products%20were%20a%20preselected%20set%20of%2025%20items%20commonly%20sold%20on%20Amazon.com%2C%20including%20packs%20of%20Oreo%20cookies%2C%20boxes%20of%20Sharpie%20pens%2C%20and%20dog%20toys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221898%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20products%20selected%20for%20Amazon's%20robotic%20Picking%20Challenge%20in%202015.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67abfbbe7bb3f854015c95a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221430%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20products%20selected%20for%20Amazon's%20robotic%20Picking%20Challenge%20in%202015.%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20The%20%26quot%3BAnalysis%20and%20Observations%20from%20the%20First%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%26quot%3B%20research%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20were%20easier%20to%20pick.%20There%20were%20simple%20cuboids%2C%20like%20a%20box%20of%20coffee%20stirrers%20or%20a%20whiteboard%20eraser.%20Others%20were%20trickier.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20box%20of%20Cheez-Its%20could%20not%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20bin%20without%20first%20tilting%20it%2C%20adding%20another%20complex%20step%20for%20the%20robots.%20Smaller%20items%2C%20such%20as%20an%20individual%20spark%20plug%2C%20were%20more%20difficult%20to%20detect%20and%20properly%20grasp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5f60453-5687-4d06-a418-7645e42db3db%5C%22%3EVacuum%20arms%20and%20'catastrophic%20failure'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20all%2026%20teams%2C%20a%20total%20of%2036%20correct%20items%20were%20picked%2C%20versus%20seven%20incorrect%20items.%20Another%20four%20products%20were%20dropped%20by%20robots%20in%20the%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20the%20teams%20scored%20zero%20points%2C%20and%20two%20teams%20couldn't%20get%20their%20robots%20working%20well%20enough%20to%20even%20attempt%20the%20challenge%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F1601.05484%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzing%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22697%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20MIT-designed%20robot%20takes%20part%20in%20an%20Amazon%20contest%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bfabd5b1834fe3116599c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22523%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20MIT-designed%20robot%20takes%20part%20in%20an%20Amazon%20contest%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProblems%20ranged%20from%20the%20highly%20technical%20to%20the%20mundane.%20Some%20of%20the%20same%20items%20came%20packed%20differently%2C%20which%20made%20them%20even%20more%20difficult%20to%20pick.%20One%20team's%20machine%20had%20a%C2%A0vacuum%20hose%20that%20got%20accidentally%20wound%20around%20the%20robotic%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20system%20having%20hundreds%20of%20components%2C%20the%20failure%20of%20any%20one%20of%20these%20could%20lead%20to%20%26quot%3Bcatastrophic%20failure%20of%20the%20overall%20system%20%E2%80%94%20as%20witnessed%20during%20the%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224601%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Researchers%20competing%20during%20the%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf8e3369253ccddf97b4f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222806%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20competing%20during%20the%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20finding%20from%20this%20first%20Amazon%20Picking%20Challenge%20was%20that%20human%20warehouse%20workers%20were%20a%20lot%20better%20than%20machines%20at%20picking%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20human%20is%20capable%20of%20performing%20a%20more%20complex%20version%20of%20the%20same%20task%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20%E2%88%BC400%20sorts%2Fhour%20with%20minimal%20errors%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20best%20robot%20in%20the%20APC%20achieved%20a%20rate%20of%20%E2%88%BC30%20sorts%2Fhour%20with%20a%2016%25%20failure%20rate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20conclusion%20was%20hopeful%2C%20too%3A%20The%20contest%20showed%20that%20robotics%20could%20substantially%20increase%20warehouse%20automation%20and%20order%20fulfillment%20in%20the%20near%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20competition%20was%20renamed%20the%20following%20year%20as%20the%20Amazon%20Robotics%20Challenge%2C%20and%20the%20tasks%20evolved%20to%20be%20more%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22922442e4-0dd1-475e-a023-61f765741d5d%5C%22%3ESuction%20and%20other%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tye%20Brady%2C%20chief%20technologist%20at%20Amazon%20Robotics%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67abfc9f7bb3f854015c95b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22743%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETye%20Brady%2C%20chief%20technologist%20at%20Amazon%20Robotics%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-robotics-tye-brady-ai-warehouse-jobs-human-common-sense-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETye%20Brady%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20chief%20technologist%20at%20Amazon%20Robotics%2C%20was%20involved%20in%20those%20later%20Amazon%20Robotics%20Challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20he%20said%20research%20on%20robotic%20manipulation%20exploded%20from%202016%20through%202018%2C%20with%20many%20institutions%20publishing%20their%20results%20and%20insights.%20This%20helped%20spread%20valuable%20knowledge%20across%20the%20industry%2C%20speeding%20up%20progress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%C2%A0least%20two%20professors%20started%20graduate-level%20classes%20related%20to%20Amazon's%20challenge%2C%20and%20these%20programs%20are%20still%20churning%20out%20experts%20with%20valuable%20practical%20applied%20knowledge%20in%20robotics%2C%20Brady%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20smart%20people%20together%20in%20a%20room%20and%20think%20about%20focused%20problems%2C%20some%20great%20things%20are%20going%20to%20happen%2C%20and%20that's%20really%20what%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%26quot%3BIt%20inspired%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20work%20that%20we%20have%20today%20that%20we%20see%20in%2C%20for%20example%2C%20our%20Sparrow%20and%20Robin%20manipulation%20systems%20that%20are%20real-world%20products%20delivering%20packages%20inside%20of%20our%20fulfillment%20centers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221535%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Robin%20operating%20in%20a%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d35c1eb4be2fff9a325fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20Robin%20robot%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20first%20competition%20in%202015%2C%20some%20robotics%20teams%20used%20grippers%20that%20mimicked%20the%20way%20a%20human%20hand%20picks%20things%20up.%20Other%20teams%20tried%20suction%20instead%2C%20with%20some%20researchers%20even%20strapping%20off-the-shelf%20vacuum%20cleaners%20to%20their%20robots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGripping%20proved%20more%20problematic%20because%20the%20robots%20didn't%20receive%20enough%20information%20to%20know%20when%20to%20release%20or%20add%20pressure%20at%20the%20right%20times.%20This%20could%20result%20in%20squashed%20or%20crushed%20products%20or%20dropped%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESucking%20the%20items%20up%20so%20they%20stuck%20to%20the%20end%20of%20robot%20arms%20was%20a%20more%20successful%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20high%20flow%20suction%20was%20novel.%20Bring%20your%20favorite%20vacuum%20cleaner%20and%20start%20picking%20up%20objects.%20That%20was%20kind%20of%20clever%2C%26quot%3B%20Brady%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20idea%2C%20we%20used%20suction%20inside%20of%20our%20Robin%20and%20our%20Sparrow%20arms.%20It's%20very%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d3db54d-dbc0-4dfa-b9cb-41894372b482%5C%22%3EThe%20boss%20has%20noticed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20unveiled%20Robin%2C%20its%20first%20robotic%20arm%2C%20in%202021.%20This%20machine%C2%A0picks%20up%20packages%20from%20conveyor%20belts%20and%20places%20them%20on%20other%20mobile%20robots%20called%20Pegasus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESparrow%20followed%20in%202023.%20This%C2%A0was%20Amazon's%20first%20robotic%20arm%20to%20handle%20individual%20items%20rather%20than%20packages.%20It%20uses%20computer%20vision%20and%20AI%20to%20pick%20more%20than%20200%20million%20different%20items%20from%20containers%20and%20place%20them%20into%20totes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon's%20robotic%20arm%20Sparrow%20lifts%20up%20items%20in%20fulfillment%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d3654196626c40986068c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon's%20Sparrow%20robotic%20arm%20picking%20products%20inside%20a%20warehouse%3Cp%3EAmazon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%20has%20taken%20notice.%20At%20the%20AWS%20re%3AInvent%20conference%20in%20December%2C%20he%20should%20have%20been%20talking%20about%20cloud%20computing.%20But%20he%20took%20time%20away%20from%20that%20subject%20to%20wax%20lyrical%20about%20Sparrow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20discern%20which%20item%20is%20which.%20It%20has%20to%20know%20how%20to%20grasp%20that%20item%2C%20given%20the%20size%20of%20it%20and%20the%20materials%20and%20the%20flexibility%20of%20that%20material.%20And%20then%20it%20has%20to%20know%20where%20in%20the%20receiving%20bin%20it%20can%20put%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20all%20inventions%20that%20are%20critical%20to%20us%20changing%20the%20processing%20time%20and%20the%20cost%20to%20serve%20our%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20has%20noticed%2C%20too.%20Morgan%20Stanley%20recently%20estimated%20that%20Amazon's%20warehouse%20robots%20could%20save%20the%20company%20as%20much%20as%20%2410%20billion%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20story%20is%20we're%20just%20getting%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brady.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse-robots-picking-challenge-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740736802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0e0f8b1834fe31165bc46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse-robots-picking-challenge-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google%20self-driving%20cars%20emerged%20from%20the%20DARPA%20Grand%20Challenge.%20Amazon's%20powerful%20picking%20robots%20were%20inspired%20by%20a%20similar%20competition%20a%20decade%20ago.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abarr%40businessinsider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr%2CEugene%20Kim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse-robots-picking-challenge-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lawsuits%20involving%20DOGE%20and%