fs%20%E2%80%94%20which%20include%20the%20advocacy%20groups%20Center%20for%20Taxpayer%20Rights%20and%20Main%20Street%20Alliance%2C%20along%20with%20workers'%20unions%20National%20Federation%20of%20Federal%20Employees%20and%20Communications%20Workers%20of%20America%20%E2%80%94%20argue%20that%20Congress%20has%20not%20granted%20DOGE%20the%20authority%20to%20view%20the%20data%20and%20that%20such%20sweeping%20access%20violates%20the%20Tax%20Reform%20Act%2C%20the%20Privacy%20Act%2C%20and%20the%20Administrative%20Procedure%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20and%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-weighs-ban-musk-doge-accessing-americans-fiscal-data-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagreed%20to%20block%20DOGE's%20full%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20IRS's%20payment%20systems%2C%20instead%20granting%20read-only%20access%20to%20anonymous%20taxpayer%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKesten%2C%20the%20law%20professor%20at%20Florida%20State%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20lawsuits%20involving%20alleged%20privacy%20violations%20like%20this%20one%20could%20fuel%20greater%20cybersecurity%20concerns%20within%20the%20business%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20may%20be%20a%20very%20novel%20kind%20of%20problem%20that%20they%20face%20where%20privacy%20information%2C%20data%20leaks%2C%20come%20not%20from%20hackers%20or%20other%20folks%20trying%20to%20obtain%20access%2C%20but%20coming%20from%20leaks%20through%20governmental%20sources%2C%26quot%3B%20Kesten%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELawsuit%20over%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20firing%20of%20Inspectors%20General%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20Robert%20Storch%20at%20desk%20looking%20pensive%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0c9efb1834fe31165b570%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%20Inspector%20General%20Robert%20Storch%2C%20seen%20here%20in%202023%2C%20was%20fired%20after%20Trump%20took%20office.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Trump's%20first%20few%20days%20in%20office%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-watchdogs-fired-trump-administration-suing-get-their-jobs-back-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efired%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20inspectors%20general%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20telling%20them%20in%20a%20two-sentence%20email%20they%20were%20being%20terminated%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Bchanging%20priorities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20termination%2C%20eight%20inspectors%20general%20from%20the%20departments%20of%20defense%2C%20veterans%20affairs%2C%20health%20and%20human%20services%2C%20state%2C%20education%2C%20agriculture%2C%20labor%2C%20and%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20sued%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20arguing%20that%20their%20firings%20%26quot%3Bviolated%20unambiguous%20federal%20statutes%26quot%3B%20designed%20to%20protect%20them%20from%20%26quot%3Binterference%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20nonpartisan%20oversight%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInspectors%20general%20%E2%80%94%20who%20conduct%20audits%2C%20investigate%20reports%20of%20misconduct%2C%20and%20look%20for%20waste%20and%20fraud%20in%20federal%20agencies%20and%20government%20contractors%20%E2%80%94%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20independent%20of%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20also%20argue%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20violated%20the%20Inspector%20General%20Act%20of%201978%20by%20not%20notifying%20Congress%20of%20their%20terminations%2030%20days%20in%20advance%2C%20and%20not%20giving%20a%20reason%20for%20their%20removal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2014%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Ana%20Reyes%2C%20who%20is%20overseeing%20the%20case%2C%20denied%20the%20inspectors'%20general%20request%20to%20be%20immedi