ming%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20combined%20with%20skyrocketing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-electricity-supply-risk-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy%20demand%20from%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20only%20increase%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDf5S1%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20monthly%20residential%20electricity%20bills%20in%202024%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EEnergy%20experts%20shared%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20factors%20driving%20energy%20costs%20and%20explained%20why%20there%20are%20disparities%20among%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e116f64-65aa-4a62-8a02-4cefb35cabc2%5C%22%3EThe%20cost%20of%20extreme%20weather%20and%20volatile%20gas%20markets%20hit%20low%20earners%20the%20hardest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20January%202020%2C%20consumer%20energy%20services%20costs%20have%20risen%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUSR0000SEHF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E34%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCPIAUCSL%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E23%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20increase%20in%20overall%20prices%2C%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20showed.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstitute.bankofamerica.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Feconomic-insights%2Futilities-update.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20median%20utility%20bill%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20electricity%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20water%20rose%206%25%20in%20January%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20double%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fcpi.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%25%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20overall%20inflation%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20cost%20increases%20have%20hit%20people%20with%20the%20lowest%20incomes%20the%20hardest.%20A%20Bank%20of%20America%20Institute%20note%20said%20that%20in%202023%2C%20US%20households%20with%20annual%20incomes%20below%20%2450%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finstitute.bankofamerica.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Feconomic-insights%2Futilities-update.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%206.8%25%20of%20their%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20natural%20gas%20and%20electricity%20costs%2C%20compared%20to%201.2%25%20for%20households%20with%20annual%20incomes%20more%20than%20%24150%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20using%20more%20fuel%20or%20electricity%20can%20spike%20customers'%20energy%20bills%2C%20analysts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20extreme%20weather%2C%20volatile%20oil%20and%20gas%20prices%2C%20and%20utilities'%20growing%20investments%20in%20the%20poles%2C%20wires%2C%20and%20big%20transmission%20lines%20that%20deliver%20power%20to%20homes%20are%20all%20contributing%20to%20increased%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreezing%20winters%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20subzero%20temperatures%20that%20blanketed%20the%20US%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20scorching%20summers%20can%20spike%20the%20demand%20for%20heat%20and%20air%20conditioning%20and%20hike%20costs.%20Utilities%20are%20investing%20in%20aging%20infrastructure%20that%20carries%20electricity%20from%20power%20plants%20to%20communities%20and%20can%20recover%20those%20costs%20from%20their%20customers.%20Oil%20and%20gas%2C%20which%20still%20supplies%20the%20majority%20of%20US%20electricity%2C%20is%20a%20volatile%20market%20vulnerable%20to%20global%20shocks%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-russia-war-americans-are-reeling-from-high-gas-prices-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20shocks%20hit%20New%20England%20hard.%20The%20region%2C%20which%20includes%20Connecticut%2C%20Maine%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20Rhode%20Island%2C%20and%20Vermont%2C%20gets%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iso-ne.com%2Fabout%2Fkey-stats%2Fresource-mix%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2050%25%20of%20its%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20natural%20gas.%20And%20unlike%20states%20such%20as%20Pennsylvania%20or%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20where%20natural%20gas%20is%20underground%20in%20the%20region%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20fuel%20for%20New%20England%20states%20is%20imported.%20This%20partly%20explains%20why%20energy%20costs%20are%20higher%20compared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%2C%20said%20Dan%20Dolan%2C%20president%20of%20the%20New%20England%20Power%20Generators%20Association%2C%20a%20trade%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDolan%20said%20wholesale%20electricity%20prices%20have%20fallen%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20but%20that's%20been%20offset%20by%20transmission%20costs%20soaring%20800%25%20between%202004%20and%202023%2C%20data%20from%20New%20England's%20regional%20transmission%20organization%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20also%20seen%20a%20dramatic%20increase%20in%20the%20spending%20at%20the%20distribution%20level%20as%20we%20build%20out%20more%20substations%2C%20poles%2C%20and%20wires%20to%20highly%20electrified%20homes%20and%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Dolan%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20combined%20elements%20%E2%80%94%20transmission%20and%20distribution%20%E2%80%94%20now%20make%20up%20the%20largest%20single%20segment%20of%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20electricity%20rates%20across%20New%20England.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDolan%20added%20that%20New%20England%20states%20have%20more%20aggressive%20climate%20policies%2C%20including%20participation%20in%20a%20regional%20cooperative%20that%20caps%20carbon%20emissions%20from%20power%20plants%20and%20requires%20them%20to%20pay%20for%20every%20ton%20they%20emit%20%E2%80%94%20another%20cost%20that's%20passed%20on%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20opposite%20coast%20in%20California%2C%20extreme%20weather%20is%20driving%20higher%20utility%20bills%2C%20which%20averaged%20%24159%20a%20month%20in%202024.%20Utilities%20have%20spent%20billions%20of%20dollars%20on%20wildfire-related%20costs%20that%20are%20partially%20being%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers%2C%20said%20Brendan%20Pierpont%2C%20director%20of%20electricity%20modeling%20at%20Energy%20Innovation%2C%20a%20non-partisan%20energy%20and%20climate%20policy%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20costs%20include%20investments%20in%20preventing%20wildfires%2C%20like%20managing%20vegetation%20that%20can%20catch%20fire%20and%20burying%20power%20lines%20underground%2C%20as%20well%20as%20legal%20liabilities%20for%20blazes%20caused%20by%20their%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c2fd5d8-f7b2-4bd9-9f5a-fa65c6ab6431%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERenewables%20can%20slow%20rising%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPierpont%20added%20that%20some%20states%2C%20including%20Colorado%20and%20New%20Mexico%2C%20have%20been%20able%20to%20moderate%20rising%20electricity%20costs%20in%20part%20by%20expanding%20solar%20and%20wind%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20the%20states%20with%20the%20cheapest%20power%20and%20lowest%20rate%20of%20increases%20have%20easy%20access%20to%20high-quality%20wind%20and%20solar%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20citing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergyinnovation.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FClean-Energy-Isnt-Driving-Power-Price-Spikes.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20authored%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohanna%20Neumann%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20Environment%20America's%20Campaign%20for%20100%25%20Renewable%20Energy%2C%20said%20states%20that%20generate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenvironmentamerica.org%2Fresources%2Frenewables-on-the-rise-dashboard%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighest%3C%2Fa%3E%20percentage%20of%20their%20electricity%20from%20renewable%20energy%20sources%20have%20electricity%20rates%20that%20are%20below%20the%20national%20average%2C%20pointing%20to%20Iowa%2C%20South%20Dakota%2C%20and%20Oklahoma%20as%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRenewables%20actually%20reduce%20wholesale%20electricity%20costs%20and%20reduce%20our%20dependence%20on%20notoriously%20volatile%20natural%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20all%20states%20that%20have%20heavily%20invested%20in%20renewables%20have%20electricity%20rates%20lower%20than%20the%20national%20average.%20Neumann%20pointed%20to%20Hawaii%20as%20one%20example%2C%20where%20she%20said%20benefits%20from%20renewables%20investments%20are%20being%20offset%20by%20continued%20reliance%20on%20imported%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20fuels%20have%20to%20be%20shipped%20to%20the%20island%20across%20long%20distances%2C%20leading%20to%20higher%20electricity%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20is%20in%20a%20category%20of%20its%20own%20because%20the%20state's%20power%20grid%20is%20isolated%20from%20other%20regional%20ones.%20A%20deadly%20winter%20storm%20in%202021%20that%20knocked%20out%20power%20and%20sent%20electricity%20prices%20soaring%20prompted%20state%20regulators%20to%20direct%20power%20plants%20to%20better%20prepare%20for%20extreme%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Texas%20has%20abundant%20natural%20gas%20resources%20and%20is%20a%20leader%20in%20solar%20and%20wind%20development%2C%20the%20state%20aims%20to%20build%20more%20fossil%20fuel%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnuclear-startups-test-clean-power-ai-texas-a-and-m-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20nuclear%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20meet%20growing%20demand%2C%20said%20Michele%20Richmond%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Texas%20Competitive%20Power%20Advocates%2C%20which%20represents%20companies%20that%20produce%20power%2C%20including%20natural%20gas%2C%20wind%2C%20and%20nuclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichmond%20added%20that%20Texas%20has%20a%20competitive%2C%20deregulated%20energy%20market%20that%20dispatches%20the%20cheapest%20power%20first%20to%20help%20offset%20some%20of%20the%20cost%20pressures.%20But%20it%20isn't%20immune%20from%20rising%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20having%20a%20diversified%20fuel%20mix%20is%20good%20for%20reliability%20because%20the%20wind%20doesn't%20blow%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20the%20sun%20doesn't%20shine%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Richmond%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20utility%20bills%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acboudreau%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ecboudreau%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-utility-bills-state-electricity-costs-inflation-gas-prices-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740733562000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf644769253ccddf97a867%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-utility-bills-state-electricity-costs-inflation-gas-prices-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Here's%20why%20Hawaii%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20and%20Alabama%20residents%20paid%20the%20highest%20utility%20bills%20in%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20